---
name: test-specialist
description: This skill should be used when writing test cases, fixing bugs, analyzing code for potential issues, or improving test coverage for JavaScript/TypeScript applications. Use this for unit tests, integration tests, end-to-end tests, debugging runtime errors, logic bugs, performance issues, security vulnerabilities, and systematic code analysis.
---

# Test Specialist

## Neuman Brain Testing Stack

**Neuman Brain uses Vitest + React Testing Library. Follow these patterns:**

### Testing Stack
- **Unit Tests:** Vitest (not Jest) - faster, native ESM support
- **Component Tests:** React Testing Library - user-centric queries
- **Test Location:** `src/**/__tests__/` or `*.test.tsx` files
- **Run Tests:** `npm run test` (watch mode: `npm run test:watch`)
- **Coverage:** Target 80%+ for critical features (stores, services, components)

### Neuman Brain Test Patterns
```typescript
import { render, screen, within } from '@testing-library/react';
import userEvent from '@testing-library/user-event';
import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest';

// ✅ GOOD: Test user behavior, not implementation
it('creates task when user clicks Add button', async () => {
  const user = userEvent.setup();
  render(<TaskList />);

  await user.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /add task/i }));
  await user.type(screen.getByLabelText(/task title/i), 'Buy groceries');
  await user.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /save/i }));

  expect(screen.getByText('Buy groceries')).toBeInTheDocument();
});

// ❌ BAD: Don't test implementation details
it('calls addTask function', () => {
  const addTask = vi.fn();
  render(<TaskList addTask={addTask} />);
  // Testing internal function calls, not user outcome
});
```

### Required Test Coverage (CLAUDE.md Rule #13)
- ✅ **New features:** Write unit tests before marking complete
- ✅ **Bug fixes:** Add regression tests
- ✅ **All changes:** Run `npm run test` and `npm run type-check`
- ✅ **Zustand stores:** Test actions and state updates
- ✅ **IndexedDB services:** Test CRUD operations, quota handling
- ✅ **Components:** Test accessibility (keyboard nav, ARIA), user interactions

### See Also
- `CLAUDE.md` Rule #13 - Verify Testing
- `docs/technical/development_principles.md` - Testing strategy
- `.claude/skills/neuman-brain-code-reviewer/` - Code quality checks

---

## Overview

Apply systematic testing methodologies and debugging techniques to JavaScript/TypeScript applications. This skill provides comprehensive testing strategies, bug analysis frameworks, and automated tools for identifying coverage gaps and untested code.

## Core Capabilities

### 1. Writing Test Cases

Write comprehensive tests covering unit, integration, and end-to-end scenarios.

#### Unit Testing Approach

